onkin</i> (see   Jenkin  ) + <i>son</i>."]}]},{"name":"Gwerful","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Traditional name composed of <i>gwair</i> ‘bend, ring, circle’ + the mutated form of <i>mul</i> ‘shy, modest’."],"variants":[{"name":"Gweirful","meanings":["Traditional name composed of <i>gwair</i> ‘bend, ring, circle’ + the mutated form of <i>mul</i> ‘shy, modest’."]},{"name":"Gwerfyl","meanings":["Traditional name composed of <i>gwair</i> ‘bend, ring, circle’ + the mutated form of <i>mul</i> ‘shy, modest’."]}]},{"name":"ferch","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: variant of   Ferg  . Compare   Verch  .","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förtsch</b> (see   Foertsch  ).","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förch</b> (see   Foerch  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Ferg","meanings":["From the vocabulary word denoting the plant (Old English <i>fearn</i>). Modern use of this word as a given name dates from the 19th century, when it is also recorded occasionally as a boy's name in the United States. In some instances the given name may be a transferred use of the surname derived in the medieval period from the vocabulary word."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Gwerful ferch Jenkin was born in Denbighshire, Wales, United Kingdom as the daughter of Seincyn \"Jenkin\" Deca ap Madog Ddu ap Gruffudd and Gwladus Moel ferch Hywel. She had at least 1 daughter with Ieuan ap Gruffudd  ap Ieuan ap Iorwerth."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","1340–Female":"1340–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1466–1530":"1466–1530","1465–Male":"1465–Surnud","1524–Female":"1524–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1524":"1524","1466":"1466","1465":"1465","1530":"1530","1340":"1340","of,Maelor Gymraeg,Denbighshire,Wales":"Denbighshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Alltgynbyd, Llanarmon-yn-Ial, Denbighshire, Wales":"Llanarmon-yn-lal, Denbighshire, Wales, United Kingd